## Objective
Set up a Windows 11 virtual machine using virtualization software.

## Tools Used
- VirtualBox / VMware Workstation Player
- Windows 11 ISO

## Steps Performed
1. Installed virtualization software
2. Created virtual machine (4GB RAM, 2 CPUs, 64GB storage)
3. Attached Windows 11 ISO
4. Installed Windows OS
5. Created local user account

## Issues Encountered
- Example: VM would not start due to virtualization disabled

## Resolution
- Enabled virtualization in BIOS

## Outcome
- Successfully created and booted Windows 11 VM
- Verified internet connectivity

## Key Concepts Learned
- Virtualization basics
- Resource allocation (CPU/RAM)
- OS installation process

